docs.abstract: Proposition 10 in California has put a new focus on an old question: whether rent control tends to ease or compound a shortage of affordable housing.
docs.snippet: Proposition 10 in California has put a new focus on an old question: whether rent control tends to ease or compound a shortage of affordable housing.
docs.lead_paragraph: A supply of housing sufficient to meet urban needs in California will not be built for decades, if ever, and right now building doesn’t seem to be helping much. Many of the newer rental buildings carry high-end prices, while stock of affordable housing is actually falling.

headline.main: Why Rent Control Is a Lightning Rod
headline.print_headline: Why Rent Control Laws Can Be Good and Bad

docs.abstract: The country has unique challenges, but other emerging markets where big borrowing fueled rapid growth and strong returns could feel the pinch of a stronger dollar.
docs.snippet: The country has unique challenges, but other emerging markets where big borrowing fueled rapid growth and strong returns could feel the pinch of a stronger dollar.
docs.lead_paragraph: For nearly 10 years now, the flood of cash from global central banks has financed shopping malls in Istanbul, booming cities in China and 100-year bonds in Argentina. Today, many of the malls are empty, property developers in China are riddled with debt, and Argentina has just submitted to a bailout from the International Monetary Fund.

headline.main: Why Turkey’s Crisis Feels Familiar for Emerging Markets: It’s the Debt
headline.print_headline: Why Turkey’s Crisis Feels Familiar For Emerging Markets: It’s the Debt

docs.abstract: Uncertain tax policy is driving people to make snap decisions they may not otherwise make. But a short-term tax benefit may not be the best choice.
docs.snippet: Uncertain tax policy is driving people to make snap decisions they may not otherwise make. But a short-term tax benefit may not be the best choice.

headline.main: 3 Tax Breaks That May Be Better in the Long Run
headline.print_headline: Tempted to Reap Short-Term Perks From New Tax Laws? Not So Fast

docs.abstract: Jerome H. Powell, the Federal Reserve chairman, says the central bank is moving carefully and is prepared to shift gears depending on economic data.
docs.snippet: Jerome H. Powell, the Federal Reserve chairman, says the central bank is moving carefully and is prepared to shift gears depending on economic data.
docs.lead_paragraph: JACKSON, Wyo. — The economy is right about where the Federal Reserve wants it, running neither too hot nor too cold, Jerome H. Powell, the Fed chairman, said in a speech on Friday as he argued for caution and risk management.

headline.main: ‘Economy Is Strong,’ Fed Chairman Says, Urging a Policy of Risk Management
headline.print_headline: Fed Chief Urges Caution as Economy Roars
